  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Baseline">Run `npm test` in `@spaarke/ui-components`. Confirm 4 failures (or fewer). Capture exact stack traces.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Fix mammoth dynamic-import mock isolation">Edit `useChatFileAttachment.test.ts`. For the "does not throw" test, wrap in `jest.isolateModules(() => { /* re-import + re-mock */ })` OR restructure the mock setup so the rejection mock activates BEFORE the cached promise resolves. Pattern docs: https://jestjs.io/docs/jest-object#jestisolatemoduleswarning--callback</step>
    <step order="3" name="Fix cross-test microtask leakage">Add `afterEach(async () => { await act(() => Promise.resolve()); cleanup(); })` to the affected describe block. This flushes pending microtasks before the next test starts. Verify removeFile + clearAll tests now pass.</step>
    <step order="4" name="Fix SSE stream completion test">Edit `SprkChat.attachments.test.tsx` `calls clearAll on successful stream completion`. Refactor to mock the SSE reader output directly (return a pre-resolved iterator that yields the `done` event immediately). This eliminates the timing dependency on jsdom microtask scheduling.</step>
    <step order="5" name="Verification">Re-run `npm test`. Target: 0 (or ≤2) remaining failures.</step>
    <step order="6" name="Confirm no production diff">`git diff --stat src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SprkChat/SprkChat.tsx` → empty.</step>
    <step order="7" name="Document">Write `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/notes/077-jsdom-timing-fix.md` with:
      - 4-failure root causes
      - Per-fix pattern applied
      - Reusable patterns for future SprkChat test additions
      - Recommendation: which tests should eventually migrate to ui-test (Chrome integration) for cleaner isolation
    </step>
  </steps>

